definitions.definition: A Deobandi Islamist and largely Pashtun religious political movement founded in Afghanistan in 1994 by mullah Mohammad Omar , which has governed the country from 1996 to 2001 and since 2021.

main_definition: A Deobandi Islamist and largely Pashtun religious political movement founded in Afghanistan in 1994 by mullah Mohammad Omar , which has governed the country from 1996 to 2001 and since 2021.

definitions.definition: A member of the Taliban movement or its militia ; a Talib .

secondary_definitions: A member of the Taliban movement or its militia ; a Talib .
